我只知道他们的一系列要求
All I know is what they said in their list of demands.

95
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:48,610
他们相信我会当选  成为总统
And they believed I would be elected president.

96
00:05:48,610 --> 00:05:51,730
但说真的  为什么  为什么是你
But really, why? Why you?

97
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:53,230
我与他们的谈判
I successfully negotiated

98
00:05:53,230 --> 00:05:55,680
成功救出了卡洛琳和梅莉莎·米勒
the release of Caroline and Melissa Miller.

99
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:58,570
-但没救成吉姆·米勒  -我没得到机会
- But not Jim Miller. - I wasn't given the chance.

100
00:06:00,050 --> 00:06:02,980
他回答问题的方式  你怎么看
What's your read on him, the way he answers those questions?

101
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,470
-他有所隐瞒  -是吗
- He's hiding something. - Right.

102
00:06:08,520 --> 00:06:09,750
但这无所谓
But it doesn't matter.

103
00:06:10,890 --> 00:06:14,960
他很现代  让总统不那么高高在上
He's modern. He makes the presidency accessible.

104
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:18,670
你难道不想看到总统候选人通宵连线吗
I mean, don't you want to see the candidate stay up all night?

105
00:06:24,660 --> 00:06:26,520
你是说弗兰西斯老了吗
Are you calling Francis old?

106
00:06:37,870 --> 00:06:40,720
多谢各位热情的掌声  女士们先生们
I appreciate the applause, ladies and gentlemen,

107
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:44,190
但我知道你们是在为你们想见的那个女人鼓掌
but I imagine it's for the woman you really came to see.

108
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:50,980
"这是危机四伏的时刻"
"These are dangerous times."

109
00:06:51,770 --> 00:06:53,580
现在确实危机四伏
These are dangerous times.

110
00:06:53,930 --> 00:06:55,490
副总统候选人
...of the United States,

111
00:06:55,490 --> 00:06:57,280
克莱尔·安德伍德
Claire Underwood.

112
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:02,150
要知道  他只比我大几岁
He's only a couple years older than me, you know.

113
00:07:14,340 --> 00:07:17,220
谢谢  谢谢你们  内华达
Thank you. Thank you, Nevada!

114
00:07:23,150 --> 00:07:26,330
我非常感谢你们一大早来到这里
I really appreciate you all coming out here this morning.

115
00:07:28,530 --> 00:07:31,670
零售式竞选真是无可替代
No substitute for retail politics.

116
00:07:31,810 --> 00:07:33,560
尤其是她的形象
Especially her brand.

117
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:35,200
谢谢
Thank you.

118
00:07:37,620 --> 00:07:39,110
能请你给我拿杯水吗
Could you get me some water, please?

119
00:07:39,110 --> 00:07:40,550
大家好啊
Hello, everyone.

120
00:07:42,150 --> 00:07:43,320
非常感谢
Thank you so much.

121
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,510
谢谢你们  你们真是太好了
Thank you very much. That's very kind.

122
00:07:46,890 --> 00:07:48,540
非常感谢
Oh, thanks so much.

123
00:07:48,540 --> 00:07:49,430
别鼓掌了
Oh, now stop that.

124
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:51,670
停下吧  别鼓了  够啦够啦
Stop it, stop it. Enough, enough, enough. Enough.

125
00:07:51,670 --> 00:07:54,190
我都脸红了  这么吹捧我
It's embarrassing, all of that adulation.

126
00:07:54,190 --> 00:07:56,920
你好  很高兴见到你  谢谢你能来
Hello, nice to see you. Thank you so much for coming out.

127
00:07:57,010 --> 00:07:58,460
非常感谢
Much appreciated.

128
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,800
-杰克  -演讲很成功  总统先生
- Jack! - Great speech, Mr. President.

129
00:08:01,810 --> 00:08:03,170
你真是把我的心里话说出来了
It's like you're saying what I'm thinking.

130
00:08:03,170 --> 00:08:06,290
这就对了  谢谢
Well, that is the idea. Thank you.

131
00:08:06,980 --> 00:08:09,230
不过话说康威的事有点让我担心啊
Uh, I'm a little worried about the Conway thing, though.

132
00:08:09,230 --> 00:08:10,460
提起了好多问题
Bringing up a lot of questions.

133
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:12,370
但没得到多少回答
But not a lot of answers.

134
00:08:12,370 --> 00:08:14,380
我们也不想在大选投票日前一天
Yeah, and we don't need to keep hearing about that article

135
00:08:14,380 --> 00:08:15,660
老提起那篇文章吧
the day before the election.

136
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:16,550
有什么办法吗
What are we doing about it?

137
00:08:16,550 --> 00:08:18,660
我们聚在这里了  杰克
Well, we're here, Jack.

138
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:22,300
我们要多握手  能扳回一个算一个
We are fighting back one handshake at a time.

139
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:24,270
格温多林  你今天真是太美了
Gwendolyn, you look absolutely stunning.

140
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:25,770
能麻烦给我照张相吗  史蒂夫
May I get a photograph, please, Steve?

141
00:08:25,770 --> 00:08:28,290
麻烦你  千万别把他照进去
Could you do this, please? Make sure you cut him out.

142
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:31,920
接下来是来自德州科珀斯克里斯蒂的杰弗
We have Jeff from Corpus Christi, Texas.

143
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:33,410
你今天怎么样  杰弗
How are you doing today, Jeff?

144
00:08:33,410 --> 00:08:35,800
我们看到那条营救行动的广告了
We saw the ad. About the rescue.

145
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:38,770
杰弗啊  这个话题我前面已经说过了
You know, Jeff, I feel like we have been through this already.

146
00:08:38,770 --> 00:08:40,770
您救了我哥哥的命  先生
You saved my brother's life, sir.

147
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,820
克雷格·斯夸尔
Craig Squire.

148
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:47,350
斯夸尔上尉  就是你哥哥
Captain Squire. That's... that's your brother?

149
00:08:51,290 --> 00:08:52,360
上尉
Captain.

150
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:57,350
还记得我吗
Remember me?

151
00:08:58,570 --> 00:09:00,820
我记得  我当然记得
I do remember. Of course I remember.

152
00:09:00,970 --> 00:09:02,790
我以为你不愿重提旧事
I didn't think you wanted talk about it.

153
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:06,150
我们挺过来了  就够了  是不是
We lived through it. That's enough, isn't it?

154
00:09:06,150 --> 00:09:09,180
我一直没机会感谢你  告诉你
I never got to thank you and tell you...

155
00:09:09,540 --> 00:09:11,990
斯夸尔上尉  换了你也会救我的
Captain Squire, you would've done the same.

156
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:15,310
我不知道  我当时在那里
I don't know. I was in there.

157
00:09:15,690 --> 00:09:18,550
他们朝我身上扔尸体  一个接一个
They were tossing bodies on top of me, one after the other...

158
00:09:19,010 --> 00:09:20,420
我死定了
I was already dead.

159
00:09:21,140 --> 00:09:24,800
不对  就好像我已经死了一次
That's not right. It's like I've been dead once already.

160
00:09:24,990 --> 00:09:27,590
但那些尸体  就那么堆在一起
But the bodies... the way they were stuck together.

161
00:09:27,590 --> 00:09:29,400
又那么热  还有味道
And the heat and the smell...

162
00:09:29,720 --> 00:09:32,130
但你还记得你把我拉出来的时候吗
But you know when you were pulling me out, remember?

163
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:34,470
我其实记不太清楚了
I... I don't remember much, actually.

164
00:09:34,470 --> 00:09:37,190
一切都发生得太快了
It all happened pretty quick.

165
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:37,920
我知道你听见了
I know you heard it.

166
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:39,800
你得打断这个问题
You have to get him out of this question.

167
00:09:39,930 --> 00:09:41,850
他不喜欢提这些事  你知道的
You know he doesn't like talking about this. You know that.

168
00:09:41,850 --> 00:09:42,510
-汉娜  -得了
- Hannah, - Come on, man.

169
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:43,900
-我们谈谈  -你肯定听见了
- let's talk. - I know you did.

170
00:09:43,910 --> 00:09:47,140
我当时只想尽快把咱们救出去
I was just trying to get us out of there as fast as I could.

171
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:49,940
克雷格  我们活下来了
Craig, we're here.

172
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:53,930
-我们挺过来了  -是  可是
- We made it. - Yeah, but...

173
00:09:53,930 --> 00:09:55,230
你得继续生活
You gotta live your life.

174
00:09:55,230 --> 00:09:56,970
谢谢您接我们的电话
Thanks for taking our call.

175
00:09:57,190 --> 00:09:58,310
谢谢
Thank you.

176
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:07,330
他说的程度还不够  他没让康威...
He didn't call him out enough. He didn't get Conway to--

177
00:10:07,330 --> 00:10:10,280
听着  他尽力了
Look... he did what he could.

178
00:10:11,950 --> 00:10:14,320
他听到了什么  他那是什么意思
What did he hear? What did he mean by that?

179
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:15,860
不知道  那是威尔和他之间的事
I don't know. It's between Will and him.

180
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:18,930
他早就想让威尔出来说清楚了  不过
He's wanted Will to come clean about it for a long time, but...

181
00:10:19,620 --> 00:10:20,820
没能如愿
it didn't happen.

182
00:10:21,530 --> 00:10:23,150
所以  看在克雷格的分上
Which is why, for Craig's sake,

183
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:24,950
我们得让他们再连线一次
we need to get them back on the phone.

184
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:28,180
哈维小姐  你跟了我们几个月了
Miss Harvey, you've been on us for months.

185
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,270
抱歉没能成功  
I'm sorry it didn't work out.

186
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,270
如果这意味着交易取消  没事
If this means the deal's off, okay.

187
00:10:32,310 --> 00:10:33,880
我们总能找个去处
We can always find a place to go.

188
00:10:33,890 --> 00:10:36,060
让我再跟他谈谈  我们可不希望他
Just let me talk to him again. We wouldn't want him to--

189
00:10:36,070 --> 00:10:38,350
天啊  我哥哥经历得够多了
Jesus Christ! My brother has been through enough.

190
00:10:38,350 --> 00:10:39,480
我们不干了
We're done.

191
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:42,350
请你离开
I need you to leave.

192
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:56,820
他做得很好
He's doing great.

193
00:10:57,380 --> 00:10:58,400
是吗
Is he?

194
00:10:59,610 --> 00:11:01,280
那广告对我们有好处
That ad's playing for us.

195
00:11:04,020 --> 00:11:06,810
听着  我是同意了
Look, I... I agreed to this.

196
00:11:07,210 --> 00:11:09,760
-但我了解我丈夫  -我知道
- But I know my husband. - I know you do.

197
00:11:09,770 --> 00:11:12,320
那些问题是意料之中的  对吗
And those questions were to be expected, yes?

198
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:15,040
斯夸尔改了主意是好事
It's a good thing Squire changed his mind.

199
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:19,190
我们今晚可以调出一些带子  拼凑点什么出来
We can pull some tape and put something together tonight.

200
00:11:19,190 --> 00:11:20,680
明早上放出来
Hit some markets in the morning.

201
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,350
等到了投票的时候
When it's time to vote...

202
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:25,850
威尔救了他的命
Will saved his life.

203
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:28,630
太过了
This is too much.

204
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:31,290
我不想再听到关于那场战争的问题了
I don't want any more questions about the war.

205
00:11:31,290 --> 00:11:32,640
不行的
That's not gonna work.

206
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,740
听着  我可以给你看数据
Look, I can show you numbers,

207
00:11:34,740 --> 00:11:36,700
可以给你看这对我们多有利
I can show you how well it's all playing for us.

208
00:11:36,700 --> 00:11:38,790
我只是说  马克  这是...
What I'm saying, Mark, is that this--

209
00:11:38,790 --> 00:11:40,670
我做这行很久了  汉娜
I've been at this a long time, Hannah.

210
00:11:41,190 --> 00:11:43,240
知道吗  当马歇尔告诉我你有空时
You know, when Marshall told me you were available--

211
00:11:43,240 --> 00:11:44,640
马歇尔和我是老相识了
Marshall and I go way back.

212
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:47,090
这时机对我们所有人都合适  对吗
The timing is right for all of us, right?

213
00:11:48,950 --> 00:11:49,750
我们非常感激
We're very grateful.

214
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:51,470
那他就会告诉你  我通常不会
Then he will tell you, I don't get involved,

215
00:11:51,470 --> 00:11:53,520
在这么晚的时候插进来
not this late in the game, unless

216
00:11:53,530 --> 00:11:55,520
除非我知道我能发挥影响
I know I can make a difference.

217
00:11:58,250 --> 00:12:00,630
所以不管威尔和斯夸尔发生了什么
So whatever happened to Will with Squire, whatever...

218
00:12:00,630 --> 00:12:03,670
-不是  -我不想知道  也不需要知道
- It's not-- - I don't wanna know. I don't need to know.

219
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:07,430
但不管那些事让他承受着怎样的痛苦
But whatever pain he's carrying about what happened...

220
00:12:09,370 --> 00:12:10,770
对我们是有利的
it's working for us.

221
00:12:11,690 --> 00:12:14,020
所以  我需要你
So, this is what I need from you.

222
00:12:14,270 --> 00:12:15,590
回去那里
To go back out there

223
00:12:15,780 --> 00:12:19,100
确保他能撑到明早
and just make sure he makes it through until morning.

224
00:12:27,870 --> 00:12:29,910
他有机会做一个好总统
He has a chance to be a fine president.

225
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:32,820
一个伟大的总统
A great president.

226
00:12:35,410 --> 00:12:36,500
那更好了
Even better.

227
00:12:39,300 --> 00:12:40,650
因为我们需要这样的总统
Because we could use one.

228
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:48,060
斯夸尔没出现在那广告里是有原因的
There's a reason that Squire didn't appear in that ad.

229
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:50,210
我还在确认细节
I'm just nailing down the specifics.

230
00:12:54,010 --> 00:12:56,760
-让道格加入吧  -他在去费城的路上
- Let's bring Doug in on this. - He's on his way to Philly.

231
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:58,910
而且恕我直言  先生
And with all due respect, sir,

232
00:12:58,910 --> 00:13:01,680
他的技能在这里并不适用
his skill set doesn't necessarily apply here.

233
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,410
你知道道格跟我多久了吗  莉安
Do you know how long Doug has worked for me, LeAnn?

234
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:06,800
不太清楚
Not exactly, no.

235
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,560
几乎是一辈子了
Well, it's just this side of forever.

236
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:09,700
我了解他的一切
I know everything about him.

237
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:12,700
他的优势  他的弱点  他的技能
His strengths, his weaknesses, his skill set

238
00:13:12,710 --> 00:13:15,340
以及他心里在想什么
and the contents of his soul.

239
00:13:16,590 --> 00:13:19,120
希望您不是在质疑我的忠诚
I hope you're not questioning my loyalty.

240
00:13:22,270 --> 00:13:25,330
我只是想了解为我工作的人  莉安
I just like to know about the people who work for me, LeAnn.

241
00:13:25,370 --> 00:13:28,770
-我很坦诚的  -我根本不信
- I'm pretty straightforward. - I don't believe that for a second.

242
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:30,810
我第一次跟道格坐下来谈
The first time I sat down with Doug,

243
00:13:30,820 --> 00:13:33,520
更像是他的坦白而非对话
it was more of a confession than a conversation.

244
00:13:33,730 --> 00:13:36,160
他跟我说了他酗酒的事  他的过去
He told me about his drinking, his past.

245
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:38,100
他对我彻底敞开了心扉
He was completely open with me.

246
00:13:39,330 --> 00:13:41,600
我不觉得我们能指望克雷格·斯夸尔
I don't think we can rely on Craig Squire.

247
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,700
那我们还有什么好说的
Then why am I still talking to you?

248
00:13:44,660 --> 00:13:47,910
我没有掩饰内心  先生
I'm not hiding the contents of my soul, sir.

249
00:13:48,330 --> 00:13:50,120
去找凡妮莎·莫里森
Reach out to Vanessa Morrison.

250
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,860
我已经联系总监了
I already reached out to the director.

251
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,440
对  但道格还没有
Yes, but Doug hasn't.

252
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:56,050
让他去做  你在康威结束他的小节目前
So have him do it and then you come up with something else

253
00:13:56,060 --> 00:13:59,020
想点别的点子出来
before Conway is done with his little sideshow.

254
00:13:59,020 --> 00:14:00,720
关于接下来的演讲
And in terms of what comes next,

255
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:03,870
我调整了开场白  缩减了正文的篇幅
I adjusted the opening remarks and cut some from the stump.

256
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:05,300
正文不用改了
The stump is just fine.

257
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:06,710
非常感谢
Thank you very much.

258
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:10,850
请给我接第一夫人
Get me the First Lady, please.

259
00:14:11,010 --> 00:14:12,870
这个嘛  简单来说就是
Well, the... the short answer is

260
00:14:12,870 --> 00:14:15,800
在民主体制下  每个人都有相同的权利
in a democracy, everyone has the same rights...

261
00:14:15,800 --> 00:14:17,310
和相同的机会
the same opportunities.

262
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:19,860
喂
Hello.

263
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:22,300
我们身边的人知道风险有多大吗
Do the people around us understand what it takes?

264
00:14:23,610 --> 00:14:25,760
我知道康威的声势起来了
Look, I know Conway's getting a bump,

265
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:28,690
但这不代表接下来的一天里我们不能扳回来
but it doesn't mean we can't surmount it in the next 24 hours.

266
00:14:28,690 --> 00:14:32,870
他们知道我们付出了多少才走到今天
Do they know what we have done to get this far?

267
00:14:33,740 --> 00:14:35,890
汤姆现在就坐在我对面
Tom is sitting across from me right now.

268
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:38,710
我才不管你对面坐着谁  克莱尔
I don't care who you're sitting next to, Claire.

269
00:14:39,660 --> 00:14:42,970
我们都在拼尽全力  全速拉票
We're all doing everything we can as fast as we can.

270
00:14:46,650 --> 00:14:48,960
我不喜欢  我不喜欢追赶别人
I don't like it. I don't like chasing this.

271
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:50,340
你下一站去哪
What's your next stop?

272
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:57,480
-我们20分钟到斯克兰顿  -你得养养嗓子
- We, uh... We're in Scranton in 20. - You need to save your voice.

273
00:15:00,050 --> 00:15:01,860
我们战场上见
I'll see you on the battlefield.

274
00:15:11,970 --> 00:15:13,500
总统怎么样
How's the President doing?

275
00:15:15,880 --> 00:15:18,230
他还把自己当个年轻人
He's acting like he's still 30 years old.

276
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:24,410
我们都是
We both are.

277
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:29,330
这是好事  还是坏事
Is that good... or bad?

278
00:15:32,010 --> 00:15:34,130
得看我们是输是赢了
That depends on if we win or lose.

279
00:15:35,900 --> 00:15:37,390
因为我是个老兵
Because I'm a vet

280
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:40,590
我还是没弄清楚到底怎么回事
and I'm still not clear on exactly what happened.

281
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:40,170
{\an8}{\pos(191.4,29.25)}威尔·康威与美国面对面

282
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:40,170
{\pos(320.7,51.75)}田纳西州克拉克斯维尔

283
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:40,170
{\pos(66,52.65)}#问康威

284
00:15:40,590 --> 00:15:41,580
我觉得具体情况
You know, I think everything

285
00:15:41,580 --> 00:15:43,710
当时在场的士兵已经说得很清楚了
has been said by the soldiers who were there.

286
00:15:43,710 --> 00:15:45,410
不对  你的飞机
No. 'Cause your plane,

287
00:15:45,410 --> 00:15:48,590
是被击落还是按计划去营救
was it shot down or was it a planned rescue?

288
00:15:48,590 --> 00:15:50,410
是计划的
Planned, yes.

289
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:53,670
但是后来计划不得不调整了
Until the plan had to change.

290
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:56,700
-我想你懂的  -我不懂  先生
- I think you get the idea. - No, I don't get it, sir.

291
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:59,050
-你是飞行员吧  -对
- You were a pilot, right? - Yes.

292
00:15:59,050 --> 00:16:01,210
那你为什么会出舱执行地面任务
So why were your boots even on the ground?

293
00:16:01,220 --> 00:16:03,160
我们的情报有误
Our intel was flawed.

294
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:10,050
情报有误  我只得介入  没办法
Our intel was flawed and I... I had to step in. I had to.

295
00:16:14,020 --> 00:16:15,240
你好  麦克
Hi, Mike.

296
00:16:16,220 --> 00:16:18,480
我丈夫是个谦虚的人
My husband is a humble man.

297
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:22,110
你是不会听到他那天英勇救人的全部过程的
You're never going to get the details of his bravery that day.

298
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:23,660
至少他自己不会说
At least, not from him.

299
00:16:25,110 --> 00:16:27,030
在我看来  他的战友说得好
To me, his comrades say it all.

300
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:30,380
威尔是个有能力应对任何状况的人
Will is a man who is equipped to deal with whatever comes at him.

301
00:16:30,650 --> 00:16:33,730
而现在  我想和你说一件更重要的事
And now, I'd like to put in a word on a more practical matter,

302
00:16:33,810 --> 00:16:35,580
这些新集中选民的投票中心
these new centralized voting centers.

303
00:16:35,580 --> 00:16:38,230
因为最近我们收到了许多来电和疑问
Because we've had lots of calls and questions.

304
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,920
无论你支持哪位候选人
Whichever candidate you support,

305
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:43,850
你一定要去投票  这至关重要
it's essential that you get out to vote.

306
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:48,110
搭邻居的车  或者联系当地的党务办公室
Ask a neighbor for a ride or call your local party office.

307
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:51,310
这场竞选太激烈  决不能掉以轻心
This race is too close for complacency.

308
00:17:07,870 --> 00:17:09,400
我选你
You got my vote!

309
00:17:13,410 --> 00:17:17,890
-安德伍德  -非常感谢
- Underwood! - Thank you so much.

310
00:17:20,370 --> 00:17:22,570
谢谢  谢谢你们
Thank you. Thank you.

311
00:17:26,290 --> 00:17:27,590
太谢谢你们了  谢谢
Thank you so much. Thank you.

312
00:17:29,670 --> 00:17:30,800
谢谢
Oh, thank you.

313
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:33,160
能麻烦你再给我拿杯蜂蜜茶吗
Could you also get me a tea with honey, please?

314
00:17:34,170 --> 00:17:36,080
-你这样还能演讲吗  -我没事
- Are you gonna be all right to speak? - Yeah, I'm fine.

315
00:17:36,090 --> 00:17:38,000
-听听你的嗓子  弗兰西斯  -别说了
- Listen to your voice, Francis. - Stop.

316
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:40,090
你这几天一直连轴转地跑
You have been running yourself into the ground,

317
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:41,620
好几天都没睡了
you haven't slept for days.

318
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:44,810
要不你给演讲开个头
Why don't you kick off the speech,

319
00:17:44,810 --> 00:17:46,790
然后交给我  我给大家解释
let me take over, and then I will explain to...

320
00:17:46,790 --> 00:17:48,260
解释说总统失声了吗
That the president's lost his voice?

321
00:17:48,260 --> 00:17:49,330
不行  你不能这么说
No, you're not gonna say that.

322
00:17:49,330 --> 00:17:52,090
这么关键的时候  可不能出这种大新闻
We're not gonna have that headline as we enter the final stretch.

323
00:17:52,090 --> 00:17:55,360
尤其那个兰斯洛特似的小白脸在那儿嘚吧个没完
Especially since Sir Lancelot is out there yapping all day long.

324
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:58,880
我倒不觉得康威是兰斯洛特
I'm not really sure that Conway's a Sir Lancelot.

325
00:17:58,970 --> 00:18:02,050
是吗  那你觉得谁是
Oh, really? Then who would you assign that role to?

326
00:18:11,880 --> 00:18:14,450
吐得我真心疼  过来一下
God, I hate to waste that. Excuse me.

327
00:18:15,110 --> 00:18:16,570
队伍里有个年轻人
There was a young man in line,

328
00:18:16,950 --> 00:18:19,200
在大厅另一边  差不多靠着第二扇门
on the other side, sort of against that second door.

329
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,420
大概一米八
Six foot tall...

330
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:24,210
-让我们单独说句话吧  -好啊
- Maybe just give us a moment. - Sure.

331
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:26,320
你能不能试试搞到联系方式
Can you see if you can get some contact information?

332
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:28,660
要是能的话把他叫出来  谢谢
Or pull him out if you can. Thank you.

333
00:18:31,170 --> 00:18:34,310
我不是想接管  我是说我们应该以搭档形象示人
I didn't mean take over. I just meant let's appear as a ticket.

334
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:37,070
-"团结还是分裂"  -弗兰西斯
- "Are we united or are we divided?" - Francis--

335
00:18:37,070 --> 00:18:39,380
"就在葛底斯堡这里  最血腥的战役之一"
"Here at Gettysburg, one of the bloodiest battles--"

336
00:18:39,390 --> 00:18:40,850
我会背你的讲稿
I know your speech.

337
00:18:41,690 --> 00:18:43,980
但你能结尾吗  你得知道怎么结尾  克莱尔
But can you finish? You have to know how to finish, Claire.

338
00:18:43,980 --> 00:18:47,450
我十分荣幸地向大家介绍
I have the distinct honor of introducing you to,

339
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:50,250
如果一切顺利的话
God-willing and the creek don't rise,

