00:33:36,540 --> 00:33:44,040
{\an8}{\pos(191.4,29.25)}威尔·康威与美国面对面

518
00:33:36,540 --> 00:33:44,040
{\pos(66,52.65)}#问康威

519
00:33:36,540 --> 00:33:44,040
{\pos(320.7,51.75)}华盛顿特区

520
00:33:37,020 --> 00:33:40,320
很高兴并非只有我还在熬夜
Well, I'm glad to hear I'm not the only one up this late.

521
00:33:39,830 --> 00:33:44,040
{\an8}{\pos(257.4,202.95)}华盛顿  白宫

522
00:33:40,320 --> 00:33:43,190
总统先生  你有问题要问我吗
Mr. President, do you have a question for me?

523
00:33:43,690 --> 00:33:46,150
不  我没有  但我可以给你个机会
No, I don't. But I thought I would give you the chance

524
00:33:46,150 --> 00:33:49,280
问我一个问题  只有一个
to ask me a question. Just one.

525
00:33:49,780 --> 00:33:52,170
我不确定我想问你问题
I'm not sure I have any questions for you.

526
00:33:52,840 --> 00:33:54,440
别害羞  威尔
Don't be shy, Will.

527
00:33:54,440 --> 00:33:56,740
毕竟  机会难得
I mean, after all, this is a rare opportunity.

528
00:33:56,740 --> 00:33:59,150
只有你和我
Just between you and me.

529
00:33:59,350 --> 00:34:01,950
只有你和我  还有其他今晚
It's just you and me and all the other Americans out there

530
00:34:01,950 --> 00:34:03,530
失眠的美国人
having trouble sleeping tonight.

531
00:34:03,530 --> 00:34:04,690
那是因为他们知道
Well, that's because they know

532
00:34:04,690 --> 00:34:07,820
明天的投票会决定他们的未来
that tomorrow's vote will decide their future.

533
00:34:08,050 --> 00:34:09,880
这就是关键问题  对吧
So that's the question then, isn't it?

534
00:34:10,750 --> 00:34:12,460
未来属于谁
Who does the future belong to?

535
00:34:12,460 --> 00:34:15,320
我觉得只有上帝能回答那个问题
Well, I don't think anyone but God can answer that one.

536
00:34:15,320 --> 00:34:18,910
我们只能在此生尽可能地证明自己
All we can do is make a case for ourselves while we're here.

537
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:22,040
好吧
Okay.

538
00:34:24,350 --> 00:34:25,670
我想问你
Here's my question.

539
00:34:28,270 --> 00:34:29,530
我成功的谈判
I successfully negotiated

540
00:34:29,530 --> 00:34:32,080
让卡洛琳和梅莉莎·米勒得以释放
the release of Caroline and Melissa Miller.

541
00:34:32,990 --> 00:34:34,720
但你插手进来
Then you stepped in.

542
00:34:35,920 --> 00:34:39,390
你没让我完成任务  为什么
You didn't let me finish the job. Why?

543
00:34:40,600 --> 00:34:42,860
你真想让我回答那个问题吗  威尔
Do you really want me to answer that question, Will?

544
00:34:42,860 --> 00:34:45,740
-我不确定你想这么做  -我很想
- Because I'm not sure you do. - Oh, I do.

545
00:34:49,700 --> 00:34:52,310
因为他们知道自己能够占你便宜
Because they knew they could take advantage of you.

546
00:34:52,310 --> 00:34:53,580
他们发现了
They saw it.

547
00:34:54,200 --> 00:34:56,480
-怎么说  先生  -他们察觉出来了
- How's that, sir? - They felt it.

548
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:58,370
无论你在海外遭遇了什么
Whatever happened to you overseas,

549
00:34:58,380 --> 00:35:01,590
你都不必感到内疚或惭愧
there's no reason to feel guilty or ashamed.

550
00:35:01,590 --> 00:35:06,090
我为国尽忠了  我那么做
I served my country. I did what I did...

551
00:35:06,860 --> 00:35:08,760
是因为我别无选择
because it's what I had to do.

552
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,760
不像某些人
Not like some others.

553
00:35:13,460 --> 00:35:16,600
我成年以来一直担任公职  威尔
I've been in public office my entire adult life, Will.

554
00:35:19,180 --> 00:35:21,890
其实我曾与你这种人是同学
The truth is, I went to school with guys like you.

555
00:35:21,890 --> 00:35:24,700
英姿飒爽  心怀善意的人
Good looking guys with good intentions...

556
00:35:25,900 --> 00:35:27,500
跟你一样
just like you.

557
00:35:27,720 --> 00:35:29,730
这是我的真心话
And I mean that sincerely.

558
00:35:30,560 --> 00:35:33,220
我还想让你知道  无论明天结果如何
And I want you to know that whatever happens tomorrow,

559
00:35:33,870 --> 00:35:36,160
我从未质疑过你的意图
I never doubted your intentions.

560
00:35:38,910 --> 00:35:42,840
现在对你来说很晚了  总统先生  休息去吧
Must be late for you, Mr. President. Get some sleep.

561
00:35:43,230 --> 00:35:46,240
恐怕我们俩今晚都很难睡得着
I doubt either of us will be getting much sleep tonight.

562
00:35:46,740 --> 00:35:48,860
谢谢你接听我的电话
But thank you for taking my call.

563
00:35:48,900 --> 00:35:50,270
也谢谢你来电
Well, thank you for calling.

564
00:35:59,940 --> 00:36:03,220
现在只剩下一个问题  一个很重要的问题
Now, there's only one more question, and it's a big one.

565
00:36:03,300 --> 00:36:05,300
只能由你们自己回答
And you're gonna have to answer it yourselves.

566
00:36:06,580 --> 00:36:09,430
谁会成为下任美国总统
Who's gonna be the next President of the United States?

567
00:36:16,810 --> 00:36:18,810
我知道我会投给谁
I know who I'm voting for.

568
00:36:20,250 --> 00:36:23,840
我想感谢办成这次24小时节目的各位
I'd like to thank everyone who made the last 24 hours possible.

569
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:25,840
全体技术人员和工作人员
All the... the technicians and crew.

570
00:36:25,840 --> 00:36:30,480
如果我们能像他们一样齐心协力  那我保证
And if we all work together the way they have, then I promise,

571
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:34,840
我们真的会为世界上最伟大的国家
we will truly make this the first of many, many new days

572
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:37,080
开启崭新的未来
for the greatest country in the world.

573
00:36:38,980 --> 00:36:43,190
早安  美国  天佑美国  谢谢
Good morning, America. God bless America, and thank you.

574
00:36:44,920 --> 00:36:47,790
下线了  好了  各位
And we're out. Okay, guys.

575
00:36:56,960 --> 00:36:58,290
你很棒
You did great.

576
00:36:59,060 --> 00:37:00,630
-你做到了  -是啊
- You did it. - Yeah.

577
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:04,090
大家都很满意
Everyone is so pleased.

578
00:37:10,410 --> 00:37:13,730
我知道很辛苦  但你挺过来了
I know it was tough, but you got through it.

579
00:37:18,230 --> 00:37:20,050
-我很为你骄傲  -谢谢
- I'm really proud of you. - Thank you.

580
00:37:26,530 --> 00:37:28,960
只是些我需要回答的问题
Just some questions that I needed to answer.

581
00:37:29,220 --> 00:37:33,290
我知道  但你做到了  你做到了
I know. But you did it. You did it.

582
00:37:42,020 --> 00:37:44,030
-真棒  -非常棒
- Great job. - That was great.

583
00:37:44,030 --> 00:37:45,670
-很出色  -谢谢
- Amazing. - Thank you.

584
00:37:52,480 --> 00:37:55,740
测试  测试  一  二  三
Testing, testing. One, two, three.

585
00:37:55,740 --> 00:37:58,510
测试  一  二  三
Testing. One, two, three.

586
00:37:59,430 --> 00:38:02,940
稍稍加大增益  混响再强点
A little more gain. A skosh more reverb.

587
00:38:04,310 --> 00:38:08,820
测试  测试  很好  很好
Testing, testing, testing. That's good. That's good.

588
00:38:10,890 --> 00:38:13,500
我想感谢美国人民
I would like to thank the American people

589
00:38:13,500 --> 00:38:15,060
今晚十分踊跃的支持
for their overwhelming support tonight.

590
00:38:15,060 --> 00:38:18,480
作为下任总统  我非常重视这份职责
As your next president, I do not take this mandate lightly.

591
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:22,280
其实  压力非常大
In fact... it is heavy as hell.

592
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:24,570
你倒是比安德伍德更有机会胜选
You got a better chance than Underwood does.

593
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:33,450
你的高跟鞋很高  布莉姬特
Those are very high heels, Bridget.

594
00:38:34,950 --> 00:38:37,700
安德伍德一败选  委员会就会解散
When Underwood loses, the committee goes away.

595
00:38:38,140 --> 00:38:39,560
你的话让我心痛
You're breaking my heart.

596
00:38:40,690 --> 00:38:41,400
我本来还期待
I was looking forward to

597
00:38:41,410 --> 00:38:44,350
听你说说道格·斯坦普的料
hearing what you had to say about Doug Stamper.

598
00:38:44,560 --> 00:38:46,490
我本来也期待跟你说的
Yeah, I was looking forward to saying it.

599
00:38:48,090 --> 00:38:49,920
我是来道谢的
I came here to thank you.

600
00:38:50,710 --> 00:38:54,330
我从网上撤掉了那个
I took it down... off the Internet.

601
00:38:56,460 --> 00:38:59,280
跟你谈这事很奇怪  毕竟
It's weird, talking to you about this. I mean...

602
00:39:01,100 --> 00:39:02,540
你看过
you saw it.

603
00:39:04,990 --> 00:39:06,560
我弟弟本可能看到的
My brother could've seen that.

604
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:08,220
我会让你想起你弟弟吗
Do I remind you of your brother?

605
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:12,350
他要年轻[当下]一些
He's a little more present.

606
00:39:12,680 --> 00:39:15,140
我的工作是展望未来
Well, it's my job to look ahead.

607
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:17,900
祝你好运
Good luck with that.

608
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:39,510
-非常感谢  -谢谢  先生
- Thank you so very much. - Thank you, sir.

609
00:39:51,030 --> 00:39:52,340
我们拿到了昨晚的数据
We have the overnight numbers.

610
00:39:52,340 --> 00:39:53,450
告诉我异常数据
Give me the outliers.

611
00:39:53,450 --> 00:39:56,140
纽约掉了两个点  新罕布什尔涨了两个点
Minus two in New York. Plus two in New Hampshire.

612
00:39:56,140 --> 00:39:57,240
都不算坏
Both not bad.

613
00:39:57,670 --> 00:40:01,160
我一直不喜欢"不好不坏"这句话
"Half-empty, half-full" is an expression I have never cared for.

614
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:03,090
你昨晚的电话有作用
The call you made last night, it's helping.

615
00:40:03,090 --> 00:40:04,550
今早登上了头条
We grabbed the headlines this morning.

616
00:40:04,550 --> 00:40:05,880
-道格  -是  先生
- Doug? - Yes, sir.

617
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:08,050
帮我联系加夫尼的萨莉·安
I want you to reach out to Sally Ann back in Gaffney

618
00:40:08,050 --> 00:40:09,740
告诉我目前的投票率
and get me the turnout so far.

619
00:40:09,740 --> 00:40:11,610
我可以告诉你全州投票率
I can get you the numbers for the state.

620
00:40:11,820 --> 00:40:14,880
我不要全州的  我要加夫尼的投票率
No, I don't want that. I want the Gaffney turnout.

621
00:40:15,210 --> 00:40:17,510
你收到陆续发来的全州数据就给我们
State numbers come in, you give them to us as they come.

622
00:40:17,510 --> 00:40:19,490
任何异常都要告诉我们
Anything out of the ordinary, you let us know.

623
00:40:19,500 --> 00:40:22,120
除此之外  没其他事了  道格
Other than that, we're done. Oh, and, Doug?

624
00:40:22,120 --> 00:40:25,430
-是  先生  -你知道去哪找我们
- Yes, sir. - You'll know where to find us.

625
00:40:30,710 --> 00:40:32,880
你担心我们刚看到的选民吗
You're worried about the crowd we just saw.

626
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:37,830
不是人数  而是热情程度
Not the size. Their enthusiasm.

627
00:40:45,660 --> 00:40:46,940
我看不见得
I don't think so.

628
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:50,960
杰里  我得待会儿回你电话
Jerry, I'm gonna have to call you back.

629
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:54,840
这份九点的投票率是我们票仓的还是摇摆州的
This 9 a.m. turnout in our base precincts or swing?

630
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:56,010
票仓的
Base.

631
00:40:56,310 --> 00:40:57,710
该死
Shit.

632
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:01,840
我的数据不同  你要不要...
I've got different numbers. You're gonna need--

633
00:41:01,840 --> 00:41:04,270
我反复确认过了
I did confirm. Twice.

634
00:41:09,110 --> 00:41:11,540
道格  是我  尽快回我电话
Doug, it's me. Call me as soon as you get this.

635
00:41:13,390 --> 00:41:16,700
你只负责车险还是都有
You handle just automobile insurance or all kinds?

636
00:41:13,390 --> 00:41:18,390
{\an3}{\pos(374,247)}《双重赔偿》

637
00:41:16,700 --> 00:41:18,250
都有  火险  地震险
All kinds. Fire, earthquake,

638
00:41:18,250 --> 00:41:19,650
失窃险  公众责任险
theft, public liability.

639
00:41:19,650 --> 00:41:22,180
集体险  工业险等等  也即将覆盖
Group insurance, industrial stuff, and so on right down the line.

640
00:41:22,760 --> 00:41:24,130
意外险
Accident insurance?

641
00:41:24,140 --> 00:41:26,250
意外险  当然  迪特里克森夫人
Accident insurance? Sure, Mrs. Dietrichson.

642
00:41:28,210 --> 00:41:29,990
希望你能告诉我那脚链上刻了什么
Wish you'd tell me what's engraved on that anklet.

643
00:41:29,990 --> 00:41:32,530
-我的名字而已  -未请教
- Just my name. - As for instance?

644
00:41:33,130 --> 00:41:37,000
-菲莉斯  -菲莉斯  我想我喜欢这名字
- Phyllis. - Phyllis, huh? I think I like that.

645
00:41:37,070 --> 00:41:38,360
咱们来这段
Let's do this one.

646
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:40,730
我开车绕着街区来回好多次了
I'd drive it around the block a couple of times.

647
00:41:41,390 --> 00:41:44,290
聂夫先生  不如你明天晚上八点半左右来吧
Mr. Neff, why don't you drop by tomorrow evening around 8:30?

648
00:41:44,300 --> 00:41:45,070
他那时候在家
He'll be in then.

649
00:41:45,070 --> 00:41:47,310
-谁  -我丈夫
- Who? - My husband.

650
00:41:47,370 --> 00:41:49,320
你不是想和他谈吗
You were anxious to talk to him, weren't you?

651
00:41:49,320 --> 00:41:50,860
本来是  但是...
Yeah, I was. But, uh...

652
00:41:51,340 --> 00:41:53,810
我都有点忘记我的来意了  明白我的意思吗
I'm sort of getting over the idea, if you know what I mean.

653
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:55,870
这个州有最高车速限制  聂夫先生
There's a speed limit in this state, Mr. Neff.

654
00:41:55,870 --> 00:41:57,370
每小时四十五英里
Forty-five miles an hour.

655
00:41:57,370 --> 00:42:00,680
-我开了多快  警官  -大概每小时九十英里
- How fast was I going, Officer? - I'd say around 90.

656
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:03,150
看来你要从摩托车上下来  给我开罚单了
Suppose you get off that motorcycle and give me a ticket.

657
00:42:03,150 --> 00:42:05,330
我这次就给你一个警告
So I'd let you off with a warning this time.

658
00:42:05,410 --> 00:42:06,800
如果我不吸取教训呢
Suppose it doesn't take.

659
00:42:07,030 --> 00:42:09,380
那估计我就得给你一拳了
Suppose I have to whack you over the knuckles.

660
00:42:09,460 --> 00:42:12,050
如果我嚎啕大哭  把头靠在你肩膀上呢
Suppose I burst out crying and put my head on your shoulder.

661
00:42:12,610 --> 00:42:15,080
如果你把头靠在我丈夫的肩膀上呢
Suppose you try putting that on my husband's shoulders.

662
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:17,090
美梦破灭了
That tears it.

663
00:42:20,680 --> 00:42:21,810
我就是没心情
I'm just not in the mood--

664
00:42:21,810 --> 00:42:22,980
不  拜托  这是传统
Oh, no. Come on, it's tradition.

665
00:42:22,980 --> 00:42:24,090
如果道格需要我们  他会打电话的
If Doug needs us, he'll call.

666
00:42:24,090 --> 00:42:26,950
是  但是这次不一样  发生了太多事
Yes, but it's different this time. There's so much going on--

667
00:42:26,950 --> 00:42:28,670
-我知道  就当我迷信吧  -我们在这里
- I know, but call me superstitious. - We're in here.

668
00:42:28,670 --> 00:42:31,790
但我们赢的每一次的选举都会这么做
But we have done this every election we have ever won.

669
00:42:32,070 --> 00:42:33,710
-拜托  -我不确定我是否明白你的意思
- Come on. - I wonder if I know what you mean.

670
00:42:34,540 --> 00:42:36,180
我不确定你是否真不确定
I wonder if you wonder.

671
00:42:40,040 --> 00:42:42,060
那是一个炎热的下午  我还记得
It was a hot afternoon, and I still remember

672
00:42:42,060 --> 00:42:44,630
那条街上金银花的气味
the smell of honeysuckle all down that street.

673
00:42:45,510 --> 00:42:47,110
我怎么知道谋杀...
How could I have known that murder...

674
00:42:47,110 --> 00:42:49,190
有时闻起来就如金银花一般
can sometimes smell like honeysuckle?

675
00:42:49,920 --> 00:42:51,150
也许你就会知道  凯耶斯
Maybe you would've known, Keyes,

676
00:42:51,150 --> 00:42:53,210
就在她提到意外险的那一刻
the minute she mentioned accident insurance.

677
00:42:53,470 --> 00:42:56,360
但我没发觉  我感觉好极了
But I didn't. I felt like a million.

678
00:42:56,580 --> 00:42:57,440
怎么了
Yes.

679
00:42:57,440 --> 00:42:59,910
我回办公室看我是否有邮件
I went back to the office to see if I had any mail.

680
00:43:01,390 --> 00:43:03,370
什么叫并不相符
Well, what do you mean they don't match?

681
00:43:04,570 --> 00:43:06,210
在我的家乡
In my home state?

682
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:11,720
你和莉安最好马上给我过来
Well, you and LeAnn better get over here right now.

683
00:43:12,690 --> 00:43:13,930
怎么了
What's the matter?

684
00:43:15,560 --> 00:43:17,480
我们今天早上得到的一些选区的数字
There's something wrong with the numbers in the precincts

685
00:43:17,490 --> 00:43:19,440
有些问题  它们并不相符
that we're getting from this morning. They don't match up.

686
00:43:20,120 --> 00:43:22,190
这在南卡罗莱纳从没发生过
It's never happened before in South Carolina.

687
00:43:26,150 --> 00:43:27,900
你没什么要说的吗
Well, you have nothing to say about that?

688
00:43:28,390 --> 00:43:30,040
我相信是搞错了
I'm sure the numbers are wrong.

689
00:43:30,040 --> 00:43:31,820
你才不那么想呢
You don't believe that for a second.

690
00:43:34,190 --> 00:43:35,890
我说不过你
I can't win with you.

691
00:43:38,040 --> 00:43:39,640
不管我说什么
No matter what I say.

692
00:43:41,070 --> 00:43:43,240
你送我回家过几次
How many times did you walk me home?

693
00:43:44,020 --> 00:43:45,240
什么
What?

694
00:43:47,900 --> 00:43:50,990
不知道  大概就几次吧
I don't know. Probably a handful.

695
00:43:50,990 --> 00:43:53,010
不  并不是几次
No, it wasn't a handful.

696
00:43:53,390 --> 00:43:56,090
一个月有18次
It was 18... in a month.

697
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:02,390
我顺路
It was on my way home.

698
00:44:04,690 --> 00:44:07,170
-你什么意思  -没什么  我正好顺路
- And what are you saying? - Nothing. It was on my way home.

699
00:44:07,170 --> 00:44:09,100
不  不是顺路
No, it wasn't just on your way home.

700
00:44:09,100 --> 00:44:10,680
我们想去艺术博物馆
We tried to go to the Museum of Fine Arts.

701
00:44:10,680 --> 00:44:13,060
-但那儿关门了  那天很冷  -对
- It was closed. It was freezing that day. - Yeah.

702
00:44:13,060 --> 00:44:15,680
-你房间里播着这部电影  -是的
- And this was on in your room. - It was.

703
00:44:16,210 --> 00:44:19,440
我让你吻我  我逼你吻我
And I asked you to kiss me. I made you kiss me.

704
00:44:19,440 --> 00:44:22,270
不  你没有逼我吻你  我想吻你的
No, you didn't make me kiss you. I wanted to kiss you.

705
00:44:24,600 --> 00:44:26,840
不管怎样  我知道我们
And anyway, I knew we were

706
00:44:26,840 --> 00:44:29,430
会携手共度余生
gonna spend the rest of our lives together.

707
00:44:29,610 --> 00:44:30,950
是的
And we are.

708
00:44:31,470 --> 00:44:33,760
无论如何  绝不后悔
No regrets, no matter what.

709
00:44:35,190 --> 00:44:35,930
那是什么意思
What does that mean?

710
00:44:35,930 --> 00:44:37,730
你那是什么意思  "无论如何"
What do you mean by that, "No matter what"?

711
00:44:38,230 --> 00:44:40,040
-你觉得我们会输  -不
- You think we're gonna lose? - No!

712
00:44:42,500 --> 00:44:43,690
不
No.

713
00:44:51,110 --> 00:44:52,420
我们是一起的吗
Are we together?

714
00:44:53,000 --> 00:44:55,330
是的  我们是一起的  无论如何
Yes, we're together. No matter what--

715
00:44:55,330 --> 00:44:58,480
不  没有"无论如何"  我们是一起的吗
No, not "No matter what." Are we together?

716
00:45:00,090 --> 00:45:02,170
我们是一起的  弗兰西斯
We're together, Francis.

717
00:45:02,350 --> 00:45:05,390
那就再不要跟我提起失败了
Then don't ever bring up losing around me again.

718
00:45:05,680 --> 00:45:09,040
-是那个男孩  -谢谢  凯耶斯先生
- That's the boy. - Thank you, Mr. Keyes.

719
00:45:12,460 --> 00:45:14,460
这是家什么公司
What kind of an outfit is this, anyway?

720
00:45:14,460 --> 00:45:15,420
我们是保险公司
Are we an insurance company

721
00:45:15,420 --> 00:45:17,010
还是一群给那种白痴
or just a bunch of dim-witted amateurs

722
00:45:17,020 --> 00:45:18,350
开保单的弱智
to write a policy on a mug like that?

723
00:45:18,350 --> 00:45:19,930
等一下  凯耶斯  他不是我评估的
Now, wait a minute, Keyes. I don't rate this beef.

724
00:45:19,930 --> 00:45:22,300
费城的投票率比他们说的要低
The turnout in Philly is lower than they're saying.

725
00:45:22,340 --> 00:45:25,000
-低多少  -我们的关键选区低30%
- How much lower? - 30% in our key precincts.

726
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:26,930
30  怎么会这样
Thirty? How?

727
00:45:26,930 --> 00:45:28,650
不只是宾州  大家都没来投票
It's not just Pennsylvania. People aren't voting.

728
00:45:28,650 --> 00:45:29,950
他们的人  我们的人
Their people, our people.

729
00:45:29,950 --> 00:45:31,730
等等  如果康威拿下了宾州
Wait. If Conway's got Pennsylvania,

730
00:45:31,730 --> 00:45:32,770
那他也会拿下俄亥俄
then he's got Ohio.

731
00:45:32,910 --> 00:45:34,790
如果他拿下俄亥俄  我们就输了
If he's got Ohio, then we lose.

732
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:36,660
-这是怎么发生的  -我去告诉他们
- How did this happen? - I'll tell them.

733
00:45:36,660 --> 00:45:38,550
这件事不用你做
That is one thing you are not doing.

734
00:45:42,190 --> 00:45:43,610
都办妥了
That was all there was to it.

735
00:45:43,610 --> 00:45:46,120
没有疏忽  没有忽略
Nothing had slipped, nothing had been overlooked.

736
00:45:46,290 --> 00:45:47,960
没有什么会暴露我们
There was nothing to give us away.

737
00:45:48,770 --> 00:45:49,470
然而  凯耶斯
And yet, Keyes,

738
00:45:49,470 --> 00:45:51,890
当我沿街走去药店时
as I was walking down the street to the drugstore,

739
00:45:52,490 --> 00:45:55,300
我突然意识到一切都会出错
suddenly it came over me that everything would go wrong.

740
00:45:55,980 --> 00:45:57,000
这听起来有点疯狂  凯耶斯
It sounds crazy, Keyes,

741
00:45:57,000 --> 00:45:58,760
但这是真的  帮我
but it's true, so help me.

742
00:45:59,330 --> 00:46:01,280
我甚至听不到自己的脚步声
I couldn't hear my own footsteps.

743
00:46:05,040 --> 00:46:06,930
就好像一具行尸
It was the walk of a dead man.

744
00:46:10,570 --> 00:46:13,110
那是我度过最长的一夜  凯耶斯
That was the longest night I ever lived through, Keyes.

745
00:46:13,210 --> 00:46:15,940
第二天事情见报后  就更糟了
And the next day was worse when the story broke in the papers.

746
00:46:17,050 --> 00:46:19,120
他们开始在办公室里谈论
They started talking about it at the office.

747
00:46:19,120 --> 00:46:21,570
第三天  你开始调查
And the day after that, when you started digging into it.

748
00:46:22,370 --> 00:46:23,400
我一直把手揣在口袋里
I kept my hands in my pockets

749
00:46:23,400 --> 00:46:25,630
因为我以为它们在颤抖
because I thought they were shaking.

750
00:46:26,390 --> 00:46:28,710
我戴了深色眼镜好让别人看不到我的眼睛
I put on dark glasses so people couldn't see my eyes,

751
00:46:28,710 --> 00:46:29,460
然后我又把眼镜摘了
then I took them off again

752
00:46:29,460 --> 00:46:31,650
他们就不会好奇我为什么要戴了
so they wouldn't get to wondering why I wore them.

753
00:46:32,750 --> 00:46:35,890
-我努力想振作起来  但是...  -谢谢
- I tried to hold myself together but... - Thank you.

754
00:46:35,890 --> 00:46:37,800
我能感觉到我的神经在崩溃
...I could feel my nerves pulling me to pieces.

755
00:46:45,050 --> 00:46:45,970
给我接南卡罗莱纳
Get me Sally Ann

756
00:46:45,970 --> 00:46:48,590
切诺基县书记官萨莉·安
in the Cherokee County clerk's office in South Carolina.

757
00:46:48,590 --> 00:46:49,770
我等着
I'll hold.

758
00:46:52,820 --> 00:46:56,770
他们把宾州的投票率高估了30%
They overestimated the turnouts in Pennsylvania by 30%.

759
00:47:00,960 --> 00:47:01,870
你好啊
Hi, y'all.

760
00:47:02,450 --> 00:47:04,510
不要叫我"阁下"
Well, now, do not call me "Sir."

761
00:47:04,520 --> 00:47:05,710
我是弗兰西斯·安德伍德
This is Francis Underwood.

762
00:47:05,710 --> 00:47:07,670
我们认识这么久了  不用来这套
We've known each other too long for that.

763
00:47:10,010 --> 00:47:12,490
那么  萨莉  今天的投票率怎么样
So, Sally, how was turnout today?

764
00:47:12,890 --> 00:47:15,720
我就想知道切诺基郡的数据
Well, I was just really actually looking for Cherokee County.

765
00:47:18,510 --> 00:47:20,710
是的  我只是想亲耳听到
Yes, I just wanted to hear it for myself.

766
00:47:21,830 --> 00:47:24,800
很好  谢谢
Great. Thank you.

767
00:47:24,800 --> 00:47:27,300
代我们跟亨利和孩子们问好
And we send our love to Henry and the boys.

768
00:47:27,940 --> 00:47:29,160
再见
Goodbye.

769
00:47:33,350 --> 00:47:36,310
-有点低  -你说"低"是什么意思
- It's low. - What do you mean, "low"?

770
00:47:42,210 --> 00:47:43,430
就是很低
Low.

771
00:49:53,510 --> 00:49:58,220
{\an8}道·斯

772
00:50:00,880 --> 00:50:02,490
我刚在想那条脚链
I was thinking about that anklet.

773
00:50:03,010 --> 00:50:04,730
你现在在想什么
And what are you thinking about now?

774
00:50:04,730 --> 00:50:06,350
我不想再想了  宝贝
I'm all through thinking, baby.

775
00:50:07,230 --> 00:50:08,710
我只是过来说再见
I just came to say goodbye.

776
00:50:08,710 --> 00:50:10,880
再见  你要去哪
Goodbye? Where are you going?

777
00:50:11,380 --> 00:50:13,380
要走的是你  宝贝  不是我
You're the one that's going, baby. Not me.

778
00:50:14,000 --> 00:50:16,370
我要在这个街角下电车
I'm getting off the trolley car right at this corner.

779
00:50:16,670 --> 00:50:19,270
别卖关子了  不管是什么  直说吧
Suppose you stop being fancy. Let's have it, whatever it is.

780
00:50:19,270 --> 00:50:20,630
好吧  我来告诉你
All right, I'll tell you.

781
00:50:21,310 --> 00:50:23,040
我一个朋友有个有趣的理论
Friend of mine's got a funny theory...

782
00:50:23,620 --> 00:50:25,530
你知道这意味着什么  是吧
You know what this means, don't you?

783
00:50:26,510 --> 00:50:28,430
这是我们的地盘
This is our house.

784
00:50:29,630 --> 00:50:31,430
我们绝不会离开
We are not leaving.

785
00:50:32,530 --> 00:50:34,200
终点站是个墓地
The last stop's a cemetery.

786
00:50:34,260 --> 00:50:44,260
{\an5}{\pos(193,150)}南北战争后  联邦政府就开始大规模  系统地向退伍军人提供一系列福利
相关的行政部门经过多次重组  从1930年的胡佛政府开始
退伍军人相关的福利发放工作  统一由"退伍军人部"负责
1944年由富兰克林·罗斯福签署的《士兵法案》  几经修改
目前仍是向退伍士兵提供福利的最重要的一个联邦法案
2017年特朗普政府提交的预算草案中  退伍军人部的预算为1823亿美元
而且美国公众对军人也非常尊敬  他们享受很多优待  优惠和优先
但许多军人从战场上归来后  无法适应普通人的生活
发展出精神或心理上的疾病  出现酗酒  吸毒等问题  甚至自杀
而退伍军人部作为一个庞大的联邦机构  运作效率低下  官僚之风盛行
屡屡爆出丑闻后  在官僚体制下  一些相关的责任人却未得到惩处
2017年4月27日  美国总统特朗普签署行政命令
在退伍军人部内成立一个新机构  加强对相关事务的监管

